main event: On 3 September 1957, an object penetrated the wall of a home in New Orleans, Louisiana.
interesting points: The object passed through a metal screen and became embedded in the wall,Approximately 1 inch in diameter and 2.5 inches long, it appeared shiny as if made of metal with no identifiable marks, The object was discovered to be a rocket-propelled test article parachute, The case includes references to physical specimens located in the Artifact Room, No other aerial objects were reported accompanying the incident.
witness description: Mr. A. A. McGee, the resident of the affected home
